Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Hangzhou, one of 
China's tourist meccas, in Zhejiang Province, is striving to 
improve its facilities and attract more tourists this year. 
  An official in charge of tourism said that the city will 
speed up the transformation of the old urban districts, 
introduce international conventions and add more cultural 
attractions this year. 
  Famous for its picturesque Western Lake, Hangzhou received 
199,800 overseas tourists last year, an increase of 8.7 percent 
over the previous year. 
  The proportion of foreign tourists rose from 37.54 percent 
of 
the total number of tourists in 1992 to 43.46 percent last year. 
  With a history of 2,100 years, Hangzhou has 49 sq [square] 
km 
of scenic spots. 

